		<title>Exclusive: For now, U.S. wants Europeans just to commit to improve Iran deal</title>

		<description>WASHINGTON/PARIS/MUNICH (Reuters) - The United States has sketched out a path under which three key European allies would simply commit to try to improve the Iran nuclear deal over time in return for U.S. President Donald Trump keeping the pact alive by renewing U.S. sanctions relief in May.<div class="feedflare">
<a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?a=B2nmOLX6a3U:c7cDIYdb8c4:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?a=B2nmOLX6a3U:c7cDIYdb8c4:F7zBnMyn0Lo"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?i=B2nmOLX6a3U:c7cDIYdb8c4:F7zBnMyn0Lo" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?a=B2nmOLX6a3U:c7cDIYdb8c4:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?i=B2nmOLX6a3U:c7cDIYdb8c4:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a>

		<title>All 65 passengers, crew feared dead in Iranian plane crash</title>

		<title>Netanyahu says Israel could act against Iran's 'empire'</title>

		<title>Turkey denies allegation of chemical attack in Syria</title>

		<description>MUNICH (Reuters) - Turkey never used chemical weapons in its operations in Syria, and takes the utmost care of civilians, its foreign minister said, after Syrian Kurdish forces and a monitoring group accused it of carrying out a gas attack in Syria's Afrin region.<div class="feedflare">

		<title>Leading SPD mayors back coalition with Merkel, poll shows</title>

		<description>BERLIN (Reuters) - Leading Social Democrat (SPD) mayors favor joining a coalition government with Chancellor Angela Merkel's conservatives, a poll showed on Sunday, boosting the prospects of the center-left party backing the alliance in a ballot starting this week.<div class="feedflare">

		<title>Swastikas, slurs daubed on Polish embassy in Tel Aviv</title>

		<description>JERUSALEM/WARSAW (Reuters) - Swastikas and profanities were daubed on the entrance to Poland's embassy in Israel on Sunday after Polish Prime Minister Mateusz Morawiecki said Jews, as well as Poles and others, were among perpetrators of the Nazi Holocaust.<div class="feedflare">
<a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?a=1KzKOSGOXAE:yqvcFzmt48Y:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?a=1KzKOSGOXAE:yqvcFzmt48Y:F7zBnMyn0Lo"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?i=1KzKOSGOXAE:yqvcFzmt48Y:F7zBnMyn0Lo" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?a=1KzKOSGOXAE:yqvcFzmt48Y:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?i=1KzKOSGOXAE:yqvcFzmt48Y:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a>

		<title>Myanmar policeman who detained Reuters pair 'did not know arrest procedures'</title>

		<title>Estonia calls for EU to spend more for defense in border states</title>

		<title>Five killed in attack on church in Russia's Dagestan: agencies</title>

<item>
		<title>Saudi Arabia welcomes push for U.N. action against Iran on missiles</title>

		<description>MUNICH (Reuters) - Saudi Arabia on Sunday welcomed a draft United Nations resolution offered by Britain, the United States and France that would condemn Iran for failing to stop its ballistic missiles from falling into the hands of Yemen’s Houthi group.<div class="feedflare">
